name: fusiontables
title: Fusion Tables API
description: API for working with Fusion Tables data.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

schemas.name: Bucket
schemas.desc: Specifies the minimum and maximum values, the color, opacity, icon and weight of a bucket within a StyleSetting.

fields.name: color
fields.desc: Color of line or the interior of a polygon in #RRGGBB format.

fields.name: icon
fields.desc: Icon name used for a point.

fields.name: max
fields.desc: Maximum value in the selected column for a row to be styled according to the bucket color, opacity, icon, or weight.

fields.name: min
fields.desc: Minimum value in the selected column for a row to be styled according to the bucket color, opacity, icon, or weight.

fields.name: opacity
fields.desc: Opacity of the color: 0.0 (transparent) to 1.0 (opaque).

fields.name: weight
fields.desc: Width of a line (in pixels).

schemas.name: Column
schemas.desc: Specifies the details of a column in a table.

fields.name: baseColumn
fields.desc: Identifier of the base column. If present, this column is derived from the specified base column.

fields.name: columnId
fields.desc: The id of the column in the base table from which this column is derived.

fields.name: tableIndex
fields.desc: Offset to the entry in the list of base tables in the table definition.

fields.name: description
fields.desc: Column description.

fields.name: kind

fields.name: validateData
fields.desc: If true, data entered via the web application is validated.

fields.desc: Identifier for the column.

fields.name: columnJsonSchema
fields.desc: JSON schema for interpreting JSON in this column.

fields.name: columnPropertiesJson
fields.desc: JSON object containing custom column properties.

fields.name: formatPattern
fields.desc:
Format pattern.
Acceptable values are DT_DATE_MEDIUMe.g Dec 24, 2008 DT_DATE_SHORTfor example 12/24/08 DT_DATE_TIME_MEDIUMfor example Dec 24, 2008 8:30:45 PM DT_DATE_TIME_SHORTfor example 12/24/08 8:30 PM DT_DAY_MONTH_2_DIGIT_YEARfor example 24/12/08 DT_DAY_MONTH_2_DIGIT_YEAR_TIMEfor example 24/12/08 20:30 DT_DAY_MONTH_2_DIGIT_YEAR_TIME_MERIDIANfor example 24/12/08 8:30 PM DT_DAY_MONTH_4_DIGIT_YEARfor example 24/12/2008 DT_DAY_MONTH_4_DIGIT_YEAR_TIMEfor example 24/12/2008 20:30 DT_DAY_MONTH_4_DIGIT_YEAR_TIME_MERIDIANfor example 24/12/2008 8:30 PM DT_ISO_YEAR_MONTH_DAYfor example 2008-12-24 DT_ISO_YEAR_MONTH_DAY_TIMEfor example 2008-12-24 20:30:45 DT_MONTH_DAY_4_DIGIT_YEARfor example 12/24/2008 DT_TIME_LONGfor example 8:30:45 PM UTC-6 DT_TIME_MEDIUMfor example 8:30:45 PM DT_TIME_SHORTfor example 8:30 PM DT_YEAR_ONLYfor example 2008 HIGHLIGHT_UNTYPED_CELLSHighlight cell data that does not match the data type NONENo formatting (default) NUMBER_CURRENCYfor example $1234.56 NUMBER_DEFAULTfor example 1,234.56 NUMBER_INTEGERfor example 1235 NUMBER_NO_SEPARATORfor example 1234.56 NUMBER_PERCENTfor example 123,456% NUMBER_SCIENTIFICfor example 1E3 STRING_EIGHT_LINE_IMAGEDisplays thumbnail images as tall as eight lines of text STRING_FOUR_LINE_IMAGEDisplays thumbnail images as tall as four lines of text STRING_JSON_TEXTAllows editing of text as JSON in UI STRING_JSON_LISTAllows editing of text as a JSON list in UI STRING_LINKTreats cell as a link (must start with http:// or https://) STRING_ONE_LINE_IMAGEDisplays thumbnail images as tall as one line of text STRING_VIDEO_OR_MAPDisplay a video or map thumbnail

fields.name: graphPredicate
fields.desc:
Column graph predicate.
Used to map table to graph data model (subject,predicate,object)
See W3C Graph-based Data Model.

fields.desc: Column-value or bucket styler that is used to determine the width of the polygon border.

schemas.name: StyleFunction
schemas.desc: Represents a StyleFunction within a StyleSetting

fields.name: buckets
fields.desc: Bucket function that assigns a style based on the range a column value falls into.

fields.name: columnName
fields.desc: Name of the column whose value is used in the style.

fields.name: gradient
fields.desc: Gradient function that interpolates a range of colors based on column value.

fields.name: colors
fields.desc: Array with two or more colors.

fields.name: color
fields.desc: Color in #RRGGBB format.

fields.name: opacity
fields.desc: Opacity of the color: 0.0 (transparent) to 1.0 (opaque).

fields.name: max
fields.desc: Higher-end of the interpolation range: rows with this value will be assigned to colors[n-1].

fields.name: min
fields.desc: Lower-end of the interpolation range: rows with this value will be assigned to colors[0].

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Stylers can be one of three kinds: "fusiontables#fromColumn if the column value is to be used as is, i.e., the column values can have colors in #RRGGBBAA format or integer line widths or icon names; fusiontables#gradient if the styling of the row is to be based on applying the gradient function on the column value; or fusiontables#buckets if the styling is to based on the bucket into which the the column value falls.

schemas.name: StyleSetting
schemas.desc: Represents a complete StyleSettings object. The primary key is a combination of the tableId and a styleId.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of item this is. A StyleSetting contains the style definitions for points, lines, and polygons in a table. Since a table can have any one or all of them, a style definition can have point, line and polygon style definitions.

fields.name: markerOptions
fields.desc: Style definition for points in the table.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Optional name for the style setting.

fields.name: polygonOptions

schemas.name: Template
schemas.desc: Represents the contents of InfoWindow templates.

fields.name: tableId
fields.desc: Identifier for the table for which the template is defined.

fields.name: templateId
fields.desc: Identifier for the template, unique within the context of a particular table.

fields.name: automaticColumnNames
fields.desc: List of columns from which the template is to be automatically constructed. Only one of body or automaticColumns can be specified.

fields.name: body
fields.desc: Body of the template. It contains HTML with {column_name} to insert values from a particular column. The body is sanitized to remove certain tags, e.g., script. Only one of body or automaticColumns can be specified.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of item this is. For a template, this is always fusiontables#template.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: Optional name assigned to a template.

methods.desc: Imports more rows into a table.

pathParams.name: tableId
pathParams.desc: The table into which new rows are being imported.

optinalQueryParams.name: delimiter
optinalQueryParams.desc: The delimiter used to separate cell values. This can only consist of a single character. Default is ,.

optinalQueryParams.name: encoding
optinalQueryParams.desc: The encoding of the content. Default is UTF-8. Use auto-detect if you are unsure of the encoding.

optinalQueryParams.name: endLine
optinalQueryParams.desc: The index of the line up to which data will be imported. Default is to import the entire file. If endLine is negative, it is an offset from the end of the file; the imported content will exclude the last endLine lines.

optinalQueryParams.name: isStrict
optinalQueryParams.desc: Whether the imported CSV must have the same number of values for each row. If false, rows with fewer values will be padded with empty values. Default is true.

optinalQueryParams.name: startLine
optinalQueryParams.desc: The index of the first line from which to start importing, inclusive. Default is 0.

optinalQueryParams.desc: The index of the line up to which data will be imported. Default is to import the entire file. If endLine is negative, it is an offset from the end of the file; the imported content will exclude the last endLine lines.
